    "The key seems to be extensive prompt engineering, including the identification of best practices and close human oversight, as suggested by Shah [18].",
    "Kwong et al.",
    "also suggest LLMs should indicate uncertainty when it is most appropriate [21].While NLP has been purported to help in diagnosis and treatment plans in other specialties [22][23][24], this capacity may be limited in plastic surgery.",
    "This is because patients usually come in for a plastic surgery consultation with a known or apparent diagnosis (i.e., breast cancer, lipodystrophy, facial aging).",
    "Even if the diagnosis is unclear (i.e., hand pain), an astute plastic surgeon will rely on the physical exam and imaging to establish a diagnosis."
